  <h2>1. Problem Statement</h2>
  <p>The tourism industry is highly dynamic, requiring businesses to understand evolving travel trends, customer preferences, and market shifts. This project uses an exploratory analytical approach targeting trend analysis, segmentation, and demand forecasting.</p>

  <h2>2. Abstract</h2>
  <p>The project aims to analyze tourism data from 2014 to 2020 to identify seasonal travel patterns, forecast demand, segment travelers, and evaluate impacts of global events like COVID-19. Tools used include Python, Pandas, NumPy, and visualization platforms such as Streamlit and Flask.</p>

  <h2>3. System Requirements</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Processor: Intel i5 or above</li>
    <li>RAM: 8 GB minimum</li>
    <li>Storage: 10 GB free disk space</li>
    <li>Software: Python 3.8+, Google Colab, Jupyter, and libraries like pandas, seaborn, scikit-learn</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Project Objectives</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Analyze tourism trends and seasonal patterns</li>
    <li>Forecast visitor numbers</li>
    <li>Understand customer preferences</li>
    <li>Improve business decisions and marketing strategies</li>
    <li>Promote sustainable tourism</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Project Workflow</h2>
  <p>Data Acquisition → Cleaning → EDA → Feature Engineering → Modeling → Assessment → Visualization → Deployment</p>

  <h2>6. Dataset Description</h2>
  <p>Structured CSV from Kaggle (2014–2020). Key features: Year, Country, Tourist Arrivals, Departures, Region, and indicators like seasonal indexes and COVID-19 impact.</p>

  <h2>7. Data Preprocessing</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Handling Missing Values</li>
    <li>Removing Duplicates</li>
    <li>Standardizing Names</li>
    <li>Formatting Data Types</li>
    <li>Outlier Detection</li>
    <li>Feature Creation</li>
    <li>Final Checks</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>8. Exploratory Data Analysis</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Descriptive statistics</li>
    <li>Time series and seasonal trends</li>
    <li>Regional comparisons</li>
    <li>COVID-19 impact</li>
    <li>Correlation analysis</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>9. Insights and Interpretation</h2>
  <p>Tourism grew steadily until 2019 and dropped sharply in 2020 due to COVID-19. Europe led in inbound tourism. Strong correlation found between GDP and tourist inflow.</p>

  <h2>10. Final Deliverables</h2>
  <ul>
